"NCIS" and its characters were introduced in a two-part episode of the CBS television series "JAG" in . The show premiered on , 2003, in the United States on CBS.
Created by Donald Bellisario and Don McGill, "NCIS" follows Supervisory Special Agent Leroy Jethro Gibbs, Senior Field Agent Anthony DiNozzo, Special Agent Timothy McGee, and Special Agent Ziva David, along with Forensic Scientist Abby Sciuto, Medical Examiner Dr. Donald "Ducky" Mallard, and his assistant Jimmy Palmer, all overseen by Director Leon Vance, as they investigate crimes involving Navy and Marine Corps personnel. The ninth season of "NCIS" concluded on May 15, 2012.
On March 14, 2012, CBS renewed "NCIS" for a tenth season which premiered on September 25, 2012. Brian Dietzen, who plays Jimmy Palmer, was promoted to series regular, starting with the 10th season. On February 1, 2013, CBS renewed "NCIS" for an 11th season.
<onlyinclude>, 225 original episodes of "NCIS" have aired.
